From Fig. 7, it is clear that many of the top-ranked candidates for the combined score will either be a schizophrenia positive, cell motility positive, or both. The cases where the node is a positive in both sets is uninteresting from a predictive sense. Instead, we focused on the candidates in the top 70 predictions (sorted by combined score g) that were unlabeled (bold) in one or both of the positive sets (Table 1). Note that all these candidates would be tied using the union method (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
